    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "When the **+a**_angle_ slanted x-annotation is used we must compensate by moving any labels and titles further away from the x-axes.  This was discovered on [the forum](https://forum.generic-mapping-tools.org/t/custom-annotations-on-the-x-axis-with-gmt-6/320/5).  For instance,\r\n\r\n`gmt basemap -R0/5000/0/20 -JX6i/3i -Bxaf+a45+l\"MY VERY LONG LABEL\" -Byaf -B+t\"THIS IS MY TITLE\" -png map`\r\n\r\nproduces the plot below, and once we move the label then the title needs to move up as well.\r\n\r\n![map](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26473567/77583108-956e6580-6e84-11ea-9190-d3cf1dffb3b6.png)",
